Quick Start (TL;DR)
If you remember nothing else, remember this:
❗ Client-visible tasks → title & description in German
❗ Client communication → German only and correct thread usage
❗ Files → links only (upload → copy link → paste into message)
❗ Set Credits field BEFORE starting work → wait for client approval
❗ Never skip INTERNAL REVIEW before client review
❗ Status CLIENT REVIEW = waiting for client action
❗ Recommendations → add tag "recommendation" to a visible task
Thread rules (very important):
To start a new client-visible conversation, begin a new comment with @client:
If a client has already started a thread, always reply inside that thread
Replies inside an existing client thread must NOT use @client: (it would be visible to the client)
Best practice: keep all client communication in one client-started thread
Everything outside these rules is considered internal communication.
If a task does not meet these rules, do not make it visible.

1. Overview
   Clients can:
   View tasks assigned to their projects
   Review and approve work
   Request changes
   Communicate via comments
   Create new task requests
   Use a dedicated support chat
   Receive real-time notifications
   Put tasks on hold, resume tasks from hold, or cancel tasks entirely
   Receive and respond to team recommendations
   Review and approve cost estimates (credits)
   The portal syncs automatically with ClickUp. Team members work only in ClickUp, while clients never access ClickUp directly.
   Portal URL: https://portal.kamanin.at
2. ClickUp Team Member Guide
   This guide is for team members working in ClickUp who communicate with clients through the portal.
   2.1 Understanding the Portal Integration
   How It Works
   Tasks sync automatically from ClickUp to the portal
   Only explicitly marked tasks are visible to clients
   Client‑visible comments are strictly filtered
   Status changes trigger client notifications
   Client actions update ClickUp in real time
   What Clients Can See
   Tasks with "Visible in client portal" enabled
   Comments starting with @client: or replies in client threads
   Task title, description, status, priority, due date
   Their own comments and uploaded files (via links or from them uploaded)
   Recommendations (tasks tagged "recommendation") in a separate section
   What Clients Cannot See
   Tasks without the visibility checkbox
   Internal team comments
   ClickUp workspace structure
   Other team members' tasks
   Any other client data
   2.2 Task Visibility Control
   Language Requirement (Mandatory)
   ❗ All tasks that are visible to clients must have their title and description written in German.
   Task title must be client-ready German
   Task description must be clear, complete, and in German
   Internal notes, drafts, or technical explanations must remain in internal comments
   If a task is not yet properly written in German, it must not be marked as visible in the client portal.
   Making a Task Visible
   Open the task in ClickUp
   Locate "Visible in client portal" checkbox
   Enable the checkbox
   When to Make Tasks Visible
   DO make visible:
   Deliverables ready for review
   Tasks requiring client input or approval
   Client‑requested features
   Milestones and key updates
   Recommendations (see Section 2.8)
   DO NOT make visible:
   Internal planning tasks
   Technical debt / refactoring
   Meetings, admin, or coordination tasks
   Incomplete or experimental work
   Automatic Visibility for Client‑Created Tasks
   Tasks created by clients via the portal are automatically:
   Marked as visible
   Tagged with "ticket"
   Created in the first list defined in the client profile
   2.3 Communicating with Clients
   Sending Messages to Clients
   Method 1: @client: Prefix (Mandatory)
   Start your comment with @client:
   @client: Guten Tag! Hier ist der erste Entwurf.
   Bitte prüfen Sie diesen und geben Sie uns Feedback.
   The prefix is not shown to the client
   Without the prefix, the comment remains internal
   Method 2: Replying to Client Messages
   Replies inside client‑started threads are automatically visible
   No additional prefix required
   Message Rules (Very Important)
   ❗ All client communication must be in German
   Clear and professional tone
   Explain what you are sending or asking for
   Ask concrete questions when feedback is required
   Avoid internal or technical jargon
   2.4 File & Attachment Handling (Critical Update)
   ❗ Important Rule
   Files can NOT be sent directly in client comments.
   The only supported way to share files with clients is via links inside the message text.
   Correct File‑Sharing Workflow
   Upload the file to the task attachments in ClickUp
   Locate the uploaded file in the task
   Click the three‑dot menu (⋯) on the attachment
   Select "Copy link"
   Paste this link into your @client: message
   Example:
   @client: Hier finden Sie das aktuelle Design:
   https://clickup.com/attachment/...
   What Happens in the Portal
   The link becomes clickable for the client
   The client can download or view the file
   The portal stays clean, fast, and consistent
   ❌ What NOT to Do
   Do NOT upload files directly in comments
   Do NOT rely on inline attachments
   Do NOT paste raw filenames without links
   2.5 Status Workflow
   Official Status Flow (with Credit Approval)
   BACKLOG
   ↓
   TO DO  ← set Credits field here
   ↓
   [AWAITING CREDIT APPROVAL]  ← client approves via portal (if credits set)
   ↓
   IN PROGRESS  ← work begins only after approval
   ↓
   INTERNAL REVIEW
   ↓
   CLIENT REVIEW
   ↓ ↘
   APPROVED REWORK
   ↓ ↗
   COMPLETE
   ❗ If a task has a credit cost, it must not move to IN PROGRESS until the client has approved the cost in the portal. The credit approval step is not a separate ClickUp status — it is a gate enforced in the portal. The task stays in TO DO until the client clicks "Freigeben".
   Status Meanings
   BACKLOG – Idea or request, not scheduled
   TO DO – Clearly defined, ready to start; credit estimate may be pending client approval
   IN PROGRESS – Actively being worked on; credit approval already received (if applicable)
   INTERNAL REVIEW – Internal QA / lead check
   CLIENT REVIEW – Waiting for client feedback
   REWORK – Changes required (client or internal)
   APPROVED – Client approved the result
   COMPLETE – Fully done and closed
   ON HOLD – Intentionally paused
   CANCELED – Will not be completed
   2.6 Credit Estimate & Client Approval
   When Is a Credit Estimate Required?
   Almost always — any task that involves billable team work should have a credit estimate set before the team begins. Exceptions are internal admin tasks or tasks explicitly agreed as free-of-charge.
   Standard Workflow
   1. Define the task, write title and description in German
   2. Estimate the credit cost (discuss with lead if needed)
   3. Set the "Credits" custom field in ClickUp
   4. Make the task visible in the portal (set to TO DO)
   5. The portal automatically shows a "Kostenfreigabe erforderlich" block to the client
   6. Wait for the client to approve in the portal
   7. Only after approval: move the task to IN PROGRESS and begin work
   ❗ Do not start work before the client approves. The approval is logged in the portal and is visible to the client — starting without approval creates a billing dispute risk.
   What the Client Sees
   An amber "Kostenfreigabe erforderlich" block appears inside the task with the credit amount
   Two actions: Freigeben (approve) or Ablehnen (decline with reason)
   After approval, a "Kosten freigegeben" comment appears in ClickUp automatically
   After decline, a "Kostenfreigabe abgelehnt: [reason]" comment appears in ClickUp
   If Client Declines
   A comment with the reason appears in ClickUp
   Discuss the scope or pricing internally
   Adjust the credit estimate or task scope if needed
   Set the updated Credits field and inform the client via @client: message
   The client can then re-approve
   2.7 Handling Client Feedback
   When Client Approves
   Status moves to APPROVED
   Task can proceed to deployment or closure
   Optional confirmation comment from client
   When Client Requests Changes
   Status moves to REWORK
   Client feedback appears in comments
   Apply changes internally
   Move back to CLIENT REVIEW when ready
   Client Feedback Identification
   Client comments in ClickUp include:
   Label: "(via Client Portal)"
   Client name
   Message
   Attached links
   2.8 Recommendations
   What Is a Recommendation?
   A recommendation is a proactive suggestion from the team to the client — for example, a performance improvement, a new feature idea, a maintenance item, or a strategic proposal that the client has not explicitly requested.
   Recommendations appear in their own section on the client's Aufgaben page, clearly separated from regular tasks, with a lightbulb icon and amber accent. The client receives a notification when a new recommendation arrives.
   How to Create a Recommendation
   1. Create the task in ClickUp as normal
   2. Write the title and description in clear, professional German
   3. Set the credits field to the estimated cost (optional but recommended — shown to client)
   4. Enable "Visible in client portal"
   5. Add the tag "recommendation" to the task
   The webhook automatically detects the "recommendation" tag and sends a "Neue Empfehlung" notification to the client. The task appears in the Recommendations section of the portal immediately.
   ❗ The task must already be visible in the portal before adding the recommendation tag. Adding the tag to a hidden task has no effect.
   What the Client Sees
   A dedicated "Empfehlungen" section below their regular tasks
   Each recommendation shows: title, description preview, status, priority, credit cost, due date
   Clicking a recommendation opens the full task detail
   Inside the task, a yellow "Empfehlung" block appears with two options:
   Annehmen (Accept) — client selects a due date, then confirms. The recommendation becomes a regular active task, credits are deducted from their balance, and the team is notified.
   Ablehnen (Decline) — client can add an optional reason. A comment "Empfehlung abgelehnt." is posted to the ClickUp task with the client's reasoning. The recommendation is removed from their portal view.
   What Happens in ClickUp After Acceptance
   Status moves to TO DO (task enters the regular workflow)
   Tag "recommendation" is removed; tag "ticket" is added
   Due date is set to the date the client chose
   Credits are deducted from the client's credit balance
   You receive a "Empfehlung angenommen" notification
   Note: an accepted recommendation has the credits pre-approved as part of the accept action. No separate credit approval step is required.
   What Happens After Decline
   A comment appears on the ClickUp task: "Empfehlung abgelehnt." followed by any reasoning the client provided
   No status change
   The recommendation disappears from the client's portal view
   2.9 Credits & Cost Approval (Reference)
   What Are Credits?
   Credits are the billing unit used in the portal. 1 credit = 1 unit of billable work (exact value defined in the client's contract). Credit costs are set per task in ClickUp using the "Credits" custom field.
   Client Credit Balance
   Clients can view their full credit balance and transaction history on the Konto page. Every accepted recommendation or approved task deducts from their balance. Ensure credit estimates are accurate before presenting them.
   The full workflow for credit approval is described in Section 2.6.
   2.10 Support Chat
   How Support Chat Works
   Each client has one dedicated support task
   Portal support messages appear as comments on this task
   Responding to Support Requests
   Open the client's support task in ClickUp
   Respond using @client:
   Message appears instantly in the portal
   Example:
   @client: Vielen Dank für Ihre Nachricht!
   Gerne erklären wir Ihnen den Ablauf kurz.
   2.11 Best Practices
   Communication
   ❗ German only
   Respond within 24 hours (on working days)
   Use @client: consistently
   Keep internal discussion internal
   Communicate delays early and clearly
   Task Management
   Mark tasks visible only when appropriate
   Keep descriptions clear and client‑friendly
   Set credit estimate before making a task visible
   Update statuses promptly
   Use priorities consistently
   Review Workflow
   Move to CLIENT REVIEW only when ready
   Include clear review instructions
   React quickly to feedback
   Never skip INTERNAL REVIEW
   Credit Approval Workflow
   Always set Credits field before work begins
   Do not move to IN PROGRESS until client approves
   If client declines, adjust and re-present — do not start work anyway
   Keep estimates realistic — a declined estimate damages trust more than a higher one upfront
   Recommendations Workflow
   Only send recommendations for well-defined, genuinely useful proposals
   Always include a description that explains the value to the client
   Set a realistic credit cost before tagging
   Monitor ClickUp for accept/decline comments after sending
   React to declines promptly — ask internally if the pricing or proposal needs adjustment
